{{Infobox bandy team | team = BSK | logo = BSK Saint Petersburg logo.png | founded = {{Start date|1936|df=yes}} | folded = {{Start date|2005|df=yes}} | league = | division = | arena = | city = [[Saint Petersburg]], Russia | coach = | website = <!-- Home --> |pattern_he1 = |pattern_la1 = |pattern_b1 = |pattern_ra1 = |pattern_sh1 = |pattern_so1 = |leftarm1 = |body1 = |rightarm1 = |shorts1 = <!-- Away --> |pattern_he2 = |pattern_la2 = |pattern_b2 = |pattern_ra2 = |pattern_sh2 = |pattern_so2 = |leftarm2 = |body2 = |rightarm2 = |shorts2 = }} '''BSK Saint Petersburg''' ({{lang-ru|БСК Санкт-Петербург}}) was a [[bandy]] club in [[Saint Petersburg]], Russia. The club was founded as «Krasnaya Zarya» ({{lang-ru|Красная Заря}}; "Red Dawn") in 1936 and switched to the name BSK in 2001 for sponsor reasons. The club played one season in the [[Russian Bandy Super League]], the top-tier of Russian bandy, in the 2003/04 season. The home games were played at [[Stadium Spartak]] in Saint Petersburg. The club colours were white and blue while the fan club was called "Red Bandy Fans".<ref>{{cite web|url= http://bandyfans.narod.ru/engl.htm|publisher= Red Bandy Fans|title= English Review about HC BSK|language= English|accessdate= 24 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hk-bsk.ru/ |publisher=web.archive.org |title=www.hk-bsk.ru/ |language=Russian |accessdate=24 July 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060620165235/http://www.hk-bsk.ru/ |archivedate=June 20, 2006 }}</ref>
The club had to cease its activities in 2005 due to financial problems of the main sponsor.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.nvspb.ru/stories/russkij_hokkej_v_peterburge_za|publisher= Невское время|title=РУССКИЙ ХОККЕЙ В ПЕТЕРБУРГЕ ЗАКОНЧИЛСЯ |date= 29 December 2005|accessdate= 24 July 2015}}, translated to English: → [https://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?depth=1&hl=en&rurl=translate.google.com&sl=ru&tl=en&u=http://www.nvspb.ru/stories/russkij_hokkej_v_peterburge_za&usg=ALkJrhjxkGisQZRNdcYCCVK8t7KqZGwlhg] "RUSSIAN HOCKEY OVER IN SAINT PETERSBURG"</ref>
