===Comedy===
Comedian [[Robert Klein]] made Capossella's race calls the subject of one of his routines, captured on his 1974 album ''Mind Over Matter.''{{citation needed|date=December 2012}}

===Film===
Scenes for the Woody Allen movies ''[[Mighty Aphrodite]]'' (1995) and  ''[[Melinda and Melinda]]'' (2004) were shot at Belmont Park, as was a paddock scene for the 1990s remake of the film ''[[Gloria (1980 film)|Gloria]]'' with [[Sharon Stone]] and [[George C. Scott]].{{citation needed|date=December 2012}}

Scenes for the movie ''[[St. Vincent (film)|St. Vincent]]'' (2014) starring [[Bill Murray]] were shot at Belmont Park.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nyra.com/belmont/boisterous-gives-connections-second-straight-g1-man-o-war-win/ |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-08-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310035726/https://www.nyra.com/belmont/boisterous-gives-connections-second-straight-g1-man-o-war-win/ |archive-date=2016-03-10 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

===Music===
Belmont has hosted a wide range of top musical acts including [[Billy Joel]], [[Kenny Rogers]], [[Natalie Cole]] and [[Blondie (band)|Blondie]]. Titled the Coca-Cola Sunset Series, these fan based events were produced by music impresario, [[Richard Flanzer]].{{citation needed|date=December 2012}}

===Television===
A January 1975 episode of the ABC sitcom ''[[The Odd Couple (1970 TV series)|The Odd Couple]]'' &mdash; entitled "Felix the Horse Player"—was filmed partly at Belmont Park, though one of the race clips on the show features the shot of an Aqueduct starting gate.{{citation needed|date=December 2012}}

A few years later, [[Dick Cavett]] took the camera crew of his [[Public Broadcasting Service|PBS]] talk show to Belmont for a look at horse racing.{{citation needed|date=December 2012}}

Belmont Park was featured in an episode of ''[[Everybody Loves Raymond]]'', in which Frank, Robert, and Ray bet on a horse named "Marie's Mouth".{{citation needed|date=December 2012}}

Belmont Park was featured on season finale of  ''[[The Amazing Race 27]]''.

