[[File:Crazyrat.jpg|thumb|The car named "Crazy Rat"]]
'''Hilo Dragstrip''' is a [[dragstrip]] located just southeast of [[Hilo, Hawaii]] at {{coord |19|40|53|N| 155|1|49|W| type:landmark_region:US-HI |display=inline,title}}. It is also called the Pana‘ewa Drag Strip.<ref>{{GNIS |1805760| Pana‘ewa Drag Strip}}</ref> Hilo dragstrip opened in 1978, and is now operated by the [[Hawaii County, Hawaii|County of Hawai{{okina}}i]].<ref>{{cite web |title= Department of Parks and Recreation |publisher= [[Hawaii County, Hawaii|County of Hawaiʻi]] |url= http://www.co.hawaii.hi.us/directory/dir_parks.htm |accessdate= February 27, 2011 }}</ref> The [[Big Island Auto Club]] and the Hawaii Drag Racing League race at the strip. The biggest race events at the Hilo Drag Strip are the BIAC Memorial Day Drags and the BIAC Tommy Thompson Labor Day Drags. The track is sanctioned by the International Hot Rod Association (IHRA) (HDRL) (since 2003) and American Hot Rod Association (AHRA) (BIAC) (since 2015)<ref>ahramotorsports.com</ref> [[International Hot Rod Motocross]] and [[kart racing]] tracks.<ref>{{cite web |title= Big Island Auto Club 1980's |author= Tom Hada |publisher= Big Island Auto Club |url= http://hawaiiandragracer.com/ |accessdate= February 27, 2011 }}</ref><!-- alas, many typos including the title -->
