{{Infobox person | name = Pablo Ramírez | image = PabloRamirez.jpg | image_size = 200px | caption = | birth_name = Pablo Ramírez | occupation =[[Sports journalist]], commentator, [[actor]], [[Association football|footballer]] | years_active = 1980 - present | religion = | website = | hair = | eyes = | height = 1.96m (6ft 5in) | weight = | parents = | siblings = }}
'''Pablo Ramírez''' (born in [[Sinaloa]], Mexico) is a Mexican [[Spanish language|Spanish-language]] [[sportscaster]] in the United States. Ramírez primarily provides [[Spanish-language]] commentary for [[football (soccer)]] matches, currently working along with [[Jesus Bracamontes]] for the US-based Spanish-language TV station [[Univision]]. Nicknamed ''La Torre de Jalisco'' (the tower of [[Jalisco, Mexico|Jalisco]]) due to his height, at 6'5"/196&nbsp;cm.
==Early career==
He started to work in PROALPHA, a company dedicated to the production of commercials spots for television in Guadalajara, Jalisco. His boss Enrique Meludis Sr. (El Compadrito) worked in this company from 1984 to 1987, building commercial spots as famous as those like Ekar de Gas, on the way from the office to recording place of Ekar de Gas spots, he liked to share radius novels with his boss and his co-worker, together they was a great work team until the team merged in cancun and left him in charge of the office.
During the early 1980s Ramírez played football as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Atletico Tecoman]] in the [[Tercera División de México|Mexican Third Division]], until a serious injury prevented him for playing football at a higher level.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Univision|author=|title=De futbolista a narrador|url=http://www.univision.com/content/content.jhtml?chid=4&schid=7322&secid=0&cid=1987237&pagenum=2|language=Spanish|date=2009-07-10|accessdate=2009-07-22}}</ref> During the 1980s Ramírez worked for [[Televisa]] and had small roles in [[El derecho de nacer (TV series)|El derecho de nacer]] and [[El amor nunca muere (telenovela)|El amor nunca muere]]. He also made a cameo appearance in the 2014 film ''[[Rio 2]]''.
