{{Infobox Sport governing body |assocname= Philippine Taekwondo Association |logo= Logo of Philippine Taekwondo Association.png |size= |sport= [[Taekwondo]] |abbrev= PTA |founded= |recognized= 1973 |association= [[World Taekwondo Federation]] |headquarters= [[Manila]], [[Philippines]] |president= Robert N. Aventajado |secretary general=Manuel Monsour T. Del Rosario, III. |website= |countryflag= Philippines |code= PHI }}
The '''Philippine Taekwondo Association''' (PTA) is the national [[Sport governing body|governing body]] for [[taekwondo]] in the [[Philippines]]. The sports body is a member of the [[World Taekwondo Federation]] and [[Philippine Olympic Committee]].
It was established in the mid-1970s.<ref>{{cite web |title=About Us |url=http://www.philippinetaekwondo.net/about-us/ |website=Philippine Taekwondo Association |accessdate=30 May 2018}}</ref>
